Hi {!Contact.FirstName},
I wanted to check in to see if you would be interested in sponsoring or exhibiting Compliance Weeks Annual Conference. I've listed some details below.
Compliance Week 2017 Annual Conference May 22 to 24, 2017, at the Mayflower Hotel, Washington DC. Conference is designed to discuss how compliance programs should function and will feature keynote presentations from key government regulators such as the SEC and DOJ.
Attached you will find:
Word doc - full list of sponsorship opportunities; PDF outline of presenting sponsorship benefits.
**Please let me know if you would like to see a list of last years attendees.
There are multiple sponsorship options. The only way to speak at the event is to participate as a full presenting sponsor. The lower level sponsorship options do not include speaking. The two main sponsorship options are:
Full Presenting Sponsorship-
-Leadership of panel session
-Leadership of small room conversation or software demonstration
-Exhibit booth
-Attendee List
-Media exposure and branding
-Participation in welcome reception
-Access to event management team to plan a dinner
-Participation in a seated lunch, ability to pick who sits at your lunch table
-Opportunity to distribute promotional materials to attendees
-Full page advertisement in brochure
-Four conferences passes, plus passes for all speakers
Exhibit Booth 15 booths total
-6x10 area in the promenade foyer
-Three conference passes
-Power strip
-Shared Wi-Fi (general conference network)
-One highboy table
-Two stools
-One 6 foot draped table (if needed)
-Trash Bin
Lastly, I should point out that the only speakers at the event are the government regulators, corporate compliance executives, academia and the sponsors. Any firm who provides compliance related services/solutions would have to become a full presenting sponsor to be on stage.
Please let me know if you have any questions! Thanks for your consideration.
Kind Regards,
